						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the temple of Uḷavi Basappa.</p>						

						<p>Thribhuvanamalla (Bijjaḷa). </p>						

						<p>The record mentions Vāsudevanāyaka and refers to the administration of Beḷvala-dēśa. It seems to refer to Aṇṇigeṟe also. It is badly damaged and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
